# Global Project Rules

<!--
  This rules file applies to the entire monorepo project.
-->

## Monorepo Structure

This is a Turborepo monorepo with the following structure:
- `apps/api/` - Backend API (NestJS, Prisma)
- `apps/frontend/` - Frontend application (Next.js)
- `packages/` - Shared packages and configurations

## General Development Standards

### Code Quality
- Write clean, maintainable, and well-documented code
- Follow TypeScript best practices
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Implement proper error handling
- Write tests for critical functionality

### Git & Version Control
- Use conventional commit messages
- Keep commits focused and atomic
- Write descriptive commit messages
- Use feature branches for new development

### Documentation
- Keep README files up to date
- Document API endpoints and interfaces
- Include setup and deployment instructions
- Document environment variables and configuration

### Performance & Security
- Follow security best practices
- Optimize for performance where appropriate
- Use environment variables for sensitive data
- Implement proper input validation

### Collaboration
- Review code before merging
- Provide constructive feedback
- Follow established coding standards
- Communicate changes and breaking updates

## Turborepo Best Practices

- Use Turborepo's caching effectively
- Define proper task dependencies
- Keep build outputs clean and organized
- Use shared configurations from packages/
- Follow the established task naming conventions